Step 1: Update the System
First, ensure your system is up to date.

sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade

Step 2: Download the Google Chrome .deb package
Use wget to download the latest Google Chrome package from the official Google repository.

wget https://dl.google.com/linux/direct/google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb

Step 3: Install the Google Chrome .deb package
Use dpkg to install the downloaded package.


sudo dpkg -i google-chrome-stable_current_amd64.deb


If there are any dependency issues, you can fix them by running:


sudo apt --fix-broken install


Step 4: Launch Google Chrome
After the installation, you can launch Google Chrome from the terminal or the application menu.

To launch from the terminal, simply run:

google-chrome


 Summary
Now I have a guide, I can always use to quickly install Google Chrome on my Ubuntu
